      "date": "2014-08-29 18:03:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nA couple of minor comments.\n\nLooking at LNetNIInit() where the error happened:\n1779         nets = lnet_get_networks();\n1780 \n1781         rc = lnet_prepare(requested_pid);\n1782         if (rc != 0)\n1783                 goto failed0;\n1784 \n1785         rc = lnet_parse_networks(&net_head, nets);\n1786         if (rc < 0)\n1787                 goto failed1;\n\nWhy get the networks, do something else, then parse it? It seems logical that get and parse should come together, e.g.:\nlnet_prepare(requested_pid);\nlnet_parse_networks(&net_head, lnet_get_networks());",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
